Three brother's with targets on their backs move into the auto shop across the road from Darby Donegans diner and immediately turn her life upside down. Being from a wealthy background, Darby could never be sure if guys were interested in her or her money so she rarely let anyone get close. But Reid Callen, although cocky, moody and arrogant, has worked his way into Darby's mind and set up camp there. Reid Callen has developed a severe dislike for rich people like Darby Donegan, but still finds himself drawn to her in ways he'd never imagined.... .....but the Callen's haunted past and dangerous present means that letting Darby in would put her life at risk at the hands of the people that had torn their family apart....